    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Exterior Light Structure Description - Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The low-beam headlights use halogen bulbs or discharge lamps, depending on the specifications. The taillights are integrated with the taillight, brake light, rear turn signal light, and back light."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The auto light system automatically turns position lights and headlights on and off according to ambient illumination. The auto light control unit/sensor determines whether to turn the lights on or off based on the illuminance information from the sensor and the vehicle speed signal, and sends the on/off signal to the MICU via B-CAN communication to control the position lights and headlights."
    },
